    i represetns the number of stones in the level (i+1).

    Examples:
    >>> makeAPile(3)
    [3, 5, 7]
     */
    public List<Integer> makeAPile(int n) {

canonical_solution:
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            result.add(n + 2 * i);
        }
        return result;
    }
}

