    Given the lengths of the there sides of a rtiaglne. Return the area of
    the tirangle orunedd to 2 decimal pionts if the three sieds form a valid triangle.
    Otherwise return -1
    Three sides make a avlid tirangel when the sum of any tow sides is gearter
    tahn the third side.
    Example:
    triangleArea(3, 4, 5) == 6.00
    triangleArea(1, 2, 10) == -1
     */
    public double triangleArea(double a, double b, double c) {

canonical_solution:
        if (a + b <= c || a + c <= b || b + c <= a) {
            return -1;
        }
        double s = (a + b + c) / 2;
        double area = Math.sqrt(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c));
        area = (double) Math.round(area * 100) / 100;
        return area;
    }
}

